    "summary": "Junior expert in the fields of climate change, CSR and circular economy. Currently focusing my energy on helping organisations measure their emissions, improve their climate action and develop Science-Based Targets (SBTs) for GHG emissions reduction.\n\nAs a mountaineer and nature lover I have always been very attracted to environmental sciences and the sustainability challenge: How can we keep benefiting from all the technological and industrial developments during the last centuries without inflicting irreversible damage to our planet?\nHowever, it was only after completing my studies in Accounting and Business administration and working a couple of years in the field that I decided to pursue my true passion,  and enrolled in the M.Sc. in Environment and Resource Management program at Vrije University of Amsterdam.  This provided me with a general basic knowledge on the field, which became deeper and more specialised after studying a II Level Master on \"Climate Change: Adaptation and Mitigation solutions\" in the Polytechnic University of Torino.\n\nMy expertise covers the field of energy transition, sustainability, climate change risks and opportunities, resource efficiency and sustainable business models. In particular, I am very interested in sustainable management, environmental footprint evaluation, GHG emissions reduction strategies and circular economy.",
